snippet: Three and a half years after Hurricane Ike, many of the trees in Galveston that were killed in the storm are being turned into outdoor sculptures, with most in residents’ front yards.
lead_paragraph: Three and a half years after Hurricane Ike, many of the trees in Galveston that were killed in the storm are being turned into outdoor sculptures, with most in residents’ front yards.

headline.seo: Galveston Trees Killed by Hurricane Ike Are Carved Into Sculpture
headline.main: What Ike Hath Done, Artists Shall Transform
